            "answer_text": "Yes it surely is. China is one of the mother country of one of the 4 big river civilization \u2014 \u9ec4\u6cb3\u6587\u660e Yellow River civilization. We import \u6f22\u5b57 (Japanese pronunciation is Kanji, Chinese one is Hanzu), \u5112\u6559 Confucianism, cloth, food, everything. Japanese culture\u2019s many parts are from China and Korea.(But we arranged it though.) Nowadays Japanese \u30e9\u30fc\u30e1\u30f3 ramen is booming in the world.It\u2019s originally imported from China, but we arranged it very much. Some Kanji phrase like \u4eba\u6c11 (people), \u5171\u548c\u56fd (republic) are invented in Japan in Meiji era by the original combination of Kanji to translate the western books.China back-imported the words and start using them as Chinese. So we are influenting each other. ",
